        {
          "question": "<p>A cotton shirt, before it reaches you, completes a long journey. Elaborate on this journey starting from cotton bolls.</p>",
          "id": 315428,
          "options_data": [],
          "solution_data": [
            {
              "id": 203118,
              "solution": "<p>The journey starting from cotton bolls to a cotton shirt is as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"1\" style=\"list-style-type: lower-roman;\">\r\n\t<li><strong>Picking:</strong> Cotton bolls burst open after maturing. The seeds covered&nbsp;with cotton fibres are handpicked from the cotton bolls.</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Ginning: </strong>The process of separating the seeds from fibres by combing is called ginning. These days ginning is done with the help of machines.</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Spinning: </strong>In spinning, fibres from a mass of cotton wool are drawn out and twisted. This brings the fibres together to make a strong yarn. Spinning is done with the help of hand-operated devices such as charkha or by using spinning machines.</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Weaving and knitting:</strong> Weaving and knitting are the two methods of converting cotton yam into cotton fabric. A cotton shirt is usually made by weaving. In weaving, two sets of yarns are arranged together to make a fabric.</li>\r\n\t<li><strong>Stitching:</strong> The cotton fabric is then stitched into a cotton shirt.</li>\r\n</ol>"
            }
          ],
          "num_solutions_data": [],
          "alternate_solutions_data": [],
          "marks": 0,
          "youtube_id": "",
          "order": 24,
          "sub_order": null,
          "name": "24"
        },
        {
          "question": "<p>Describe the two main processes of making fabric from yarn.</p>",
          "id": 159683,
          "options_data": [],
          "solution_data": [
            {
              "id": 80978,
              "solution": "<p>Weaving is the process which involves arranging two sets of yarns together to make a fabric. It can also be done using hand operated or power operated looms. Knitting is a process done by hand or by machines. Socks , pullover and many other clothing items are the result of knitted fabrics.</p>"
            }
          ],
